prompt: Generate Cisco IOS XR 7.0.1 telemetry model-driven configuration for platform inventory + hardware state (FRU inventory entities + operational status). Use gRPC with no TLS. Server 192.0.2.124 port 57500. Use a 2-minute sample interval.
candidate:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group PLATFORM-INVENTORY
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/subscriptions/subscription/state
  sensor-path Cisco-IOS-XR-telemetry-model-driven-oper:telemetry-model-driven/subscriptions/subscription/subscription/source-interface/state
 !
 destination-group DG-GRPC
  address-family ipv4
   destination 192.0.2.124
    port 57500
    encoding self-describing-gpb
    protocol grpc no-tls
 !
 subscription PLATFORM-STATE
  sensor-group-id PLATFORM-INVENTORY sample-interval 120000
  destination-group-id DG-GRPC
 !
rationale: The candidate config matches the IP, port, transport (grpc no-tls), and encoding requirements. However, the sensor-paths are unrelated to the requested platform inventory and hardware state; instead, they reference telemetry-model-driven subscriptions state, which is incorrect. The sensor-group and destination-group names differ but that is acceptable. The sample interval is correctly set to 120000 ms (2 minutes). Due to the incorrect sensor-paths, the configuration does not fulfill the core telemetry data requirements.

prompt: Generate Cisco IOS XR 7.0.1 telemetry configuration to stream IPv6 Neighbor Discovery host addresses (host-addresses/host-address) and ND interface state. Use gRPC no TLS. Collector 192.0.2.182:57500. Sample every 30 seconds.
candidate:
telemetry model-driven
 sensor-group ND-NEIGHBOR-DISCOVERY
  sensor-path telemetry-model-driven-oper:host-addresses/host-address
  sensor-path telemetry-model-driven-oper:nd-interface-state
 !
 destination-group DG-GRPC
  address-family ipv6
   destination 192.0.2.182
    port 57500
    encoding self-describing-gpb
    protocol grpc no-tls
 !
 subscription ND-NEIGHBOR-SUB
  sensor-group-id ND-NEIGHBOR-DISCOVERY sample-interval 30000
  destination-group-id DG-GRPC
 !
rationale: The candidate config correctly uses gRPC no-tls, the correct IP (192.0.2.182), and port (57500), and sets sample-interval to 30000 ms as requested. However, the sensor-paths are generic and do not match the expected detailed IOS XR IPv6 ND operational paths. Also, the destination-group address-family is set to ipv6 instead of ipv4 as in the expectation, which is a minor discrepancy but notable. Overall, the config meets transport and destination requirements but the sensor-paths are not aligned with the expected IOS XR telemetry model for IPv6 ND, leading to a low score.
